1
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:13,067
<i>If I were you, I'd go
to the party to show them</i>

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,667
<i> I'm responsible.</i>

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,300
<i>Then maybe they'd stop being
so strict and controlling.</i>

4
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,567
<i> Just one moment with no drama.</i>

5
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,033
<i> Ma'am Marj, Sir Paolo.</i>

6
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,333
<i> Jasmine is missing!</i>

7
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>What? They got into
an accident?</i>

8
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:27,600
<i>Jasmine would never have
run away</i>

9
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:29,100
<i> if you hadn't fueled the idea!</i>

10
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:30,800
<i> You're good at that, right?</i>

11
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:34,100
<i>You blame everyone else,
you play the victim,</i>

12
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:37,467
<i>but you can't see
that you're partly at fault!</i>

13
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,933
<i>You just can't accept
that your daughter ran away</i>

14
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:42,000
<i> because you're way too strict.</i>

15
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:43,667
<i> That's enough, Thea.</i>

16
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,633
<i>You know what? We're not getting
anywhere blaming each other.</i>

17
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:55,100
Your daughter suffered
minor abrasions.

18
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,533
Nothing to worry.

19
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,667
As for Jasmine, we'll refer her

20
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,400
to her attending physician.

21
00:01:01,533 --> 00:01:03,000
Excuse me.

22
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,767
Ah, Doc, excuse me.

23
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,600
Ashley...

24
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:10,233
your dad's here.

25
00:01:10,933 --> 00:01:12,900
Don't worry, okay?
Don't be scared.

26
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:20,400
Jasmine, why did you leave
the house without telling us?

27
00:01:23,767 --> 00:01:26,100
Mom, I'm sorry.

28
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:33,400
I don't even know what to do
with you anymore.

29
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,433
Do you know how scared
I was that time

30
00:01:36,567 --> 00:01:38,900
you almost took the car
without permission?

31
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,200
And then you did it anyway.

32
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,200
Look what happened,
you got hurt.

33
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,267
This is exactly why I keep
telling you

34
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:47,500
you're not allowed
to do these things.

35
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,300
Marj, take it easy on her.

36
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:53,333
She's been through
a lot tonight, please.

37
00:01:53,933 --> 00:01:56,000
Paolo, I just want to
understand.

38
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,033
Why did you do this, Jas?

39
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,867
You knew it was forbidden,
you knew it was dangerous.

40
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:07,333
Is it still me?
Am I the problem?

41
00:02:07,867 --> 00:02:09,300
Is there something I haven't
done?

42
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,867
Honey, talk to me.

43
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:14,067
What am I not seeing?
Tell me,

44
00:02:14,233 --> 00:02:16,100
so we don't have to go through
this again.

45
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:21,967
<i>You should focus on being an
academic achiever.</i>

46
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:24,833
<i>No Torrecampo
as a starving artist.</i>

47
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:25,900
<i> I'm throwing these away</i>

48
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,067
<i>before your life ends up
in the trash, too!</i>

49
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,633
<i>- Don't!
- I won't allow it!</i>

50
00:02:29,767 --> 00:02:31,933
<i> Those drawings are mine.</i>

51
00:02:32,667 --> 00:02:34,500
<i> Why did you do that, Jas?</i>

52
00:02:34,633 --> 00:02:35,733
<i> We're best friends.</i>

53
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:37,333
<i>And that's what best friends do.</i>

54
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:39,100
<i> We've got each other's backs.</i>

55
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:40,900
<i> I'll never forget this.</i>

56
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:43,900
Auntie Marj...

57
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,033
It was me.

58
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:51,900
Ashley.

59
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,333
What do you mean it was you?

60
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:01,133
I was the one
who asked Jasmine to come.

61
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,500
Sneaking out was my idea.

62
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:14,833
I forced her to come with me.

63
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,333
It's true, Auntie Marj.

64
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,333
I forced her.

65
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,300
This is my fault.

66
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,867
I just didn't want to go alone,
so I asked her to come with me.

67
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:45,200
Ashley, you shouldn't have
done that.

68
00:04:45,933 --> 00:04:47,567
If you really wanted to go
to that party,

69
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,333
you could've told me.

70
00:04:49,467 --> 00:04:50,667
I would've taken you myself.

71
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,767
I thought you were a good kid.

72
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,067
Responsible.

73
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,100
But you're the one turning out
to be a bad influence

74
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:57,233
on my daughter?

75
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:58,733
What exactly are you trying
to do?

76
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:00,000
Do you want my daughter
to get hurt?

77
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,833
Marj...

78
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,200
take it easy.

79
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,500
My daughter was in that
accident, too.

80
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:08,333
Give her a break.

81
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,500
Marj.

82
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:21,167
Marj.

83
00:05:33,567 --> 00:05:34,567
Is Ashley fine?

84
00:05:35,033 --> 00:05:36,933
- She is okay.
- There are no injuries or...

85
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,833
Oh my God, I was so worried.

86
00:05:38,967 --> 00:05:40,000
Thank you, Doctor.

87
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:43,500
Is this what you're teaching
your daughter?

88
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,500
Is this what you're teaching
Ashley?

89
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:49,600
How to manipulate people
and be a bad influence?

90
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:51,133
Jasmine was minding her own
business,

91
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,933
but because of Ashley's
encouragement,

92
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,000
my daughter almost got killed.

93
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:57,267
Oh, please, Marj.

94
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:00,133
Are you seriously not going
to stop blaming my daughter?

95
00:06:01,167 --> 00:06:02,800
You're forgetting something.

96
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:05,500
Jasmine was the one driving the
car.

97
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:07,600
So if they got into an accident,

98
00:06:07,767 --> 00:06:10,033
it was clearly her fault.

99
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:11,933
Yes, Jasmine was driving.

100
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:13,433
But she was probably
pressured into it

101
00:06:13,567 --> 00:06:15,433
because your daughter forced
her.

102
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:17,500
She admitted it herself.

103
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:18,967
Ask Edward if you want.

104
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:25,033
Maybe Ashley only admitted it

105
00:06:25,167 --> 00:06:26,933
because she's scared of you.

106
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:29,767
The kid probably panicked.

107
00:06:30,367 --> 00:06:31,267
I mean, look at you.

108
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,533
You were practically breathing
fire at her.

109
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:34,333
Who wouldn't just say yes,
what are you accusing them of?

110
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:37,100
If you can't discipline
your daughter,

111
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:39,833
then just tell her to stay away
from mine.

112
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,133
Or else.

113
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,067
Or else what?

114
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,167
What are you going to do?

115
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:47,600
Run to Mom and Dad and complain?

116
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,100
Make Ashley look like
the villain

117
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:52,500
so we get kicked out
of the mansion?

118
00:06:54,433 --> 00:06:56,500
Go ahead.

119
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,900
You'll be dealing with me.

120
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:01,833
You think I'm scared of you?

121
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:05,867
I'm not scared
of you either, Marj.

122
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,833
I covered for you with Dad.

123
00:07:11,967 --> 00:07:14,467
I never told him those death
threats were fake

124
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:16,600
because I was worried
about you and Ashley.

125
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:19,033
And this is how it turns out?

126
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,200
Oh, really?

127
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:21,767
The way you talk,

128
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,000
it's like you're the only one
hurting here.

129
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:27,133
My daughter got hurt, too!

130
00:07:27,267 --> 00:07:30,333
None of this would've happened
if it weren't for your daughter!

131
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:31,933
You're going too far.

132
00:07:32,067 --> 00:07:33,767
Why are you always blaming
someone else, huh?

133
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:34,833
Thea!

134
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:36,067
That's enough.

135
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,167
Aren't you two embarrassed?

136
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:39,733
- Thea!
- People are watching.

137
00:07:39,867 --> 00:07:41,033
Just calm down.

138
00:07:41,167 --> 00:07:43,167
Throwing blame around right now
is pointless.

139
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:45,167
The accident already happened,
we can't undo it.

140
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:47,967
Let's focus on taking care
of the kids first

141
00:07:48,133 --> 00:07:51,533
before we start lecturing them,
so this doesn't happen again.

142
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,967
Let's just move Ashley
to another room.

143
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,900
I don't want her next
to someone's daughter here.

144
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:01,367
Who knows, if something
happens again,

145
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,133
Ashley might end up getting
blamed all over again.

146
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,367
Thea...

147
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:21,733
Why is your dad taking so long
at billing?

148
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:24,133
Is he paying in coins?

149
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:26,400
It's so late.

150
00:08:26,533 --> 00:08:28,433
I just want this night
to be over.

151
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:30,600
And look at me.

152
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:32,433
I didn't even get the chance
to change clothes.

153
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:38,767
You!

154
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,000
What were you thinking?

155
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:44,700
Do you want your grandparents
to think you're a troublemaker?

156
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:47,567
How are we supposed
to win them over

157
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,500
if this is what you're showing
them?

158
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:57,133
I wasn't trying to look like
a troublemaker.

159
00:08:58,533 --> 00:09:00,067
Then why did you do it?

160
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,167
What, you two just wanted to go
on a little field trip?

161
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:07,433
She just needs to be observed
overnight.

162
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:09,900
Then tomorrow morning,
she can go home.

163
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,067
Thank you, Doctor.

164
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,933
How about the other patient?

165
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:16,933
Ashley, my niece?

166
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:17,967
She's cleared, too.

167
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,133
I actually just discharged her.

168
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,433
I'll just finish my rounds,

169
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,700
then I'll come back to check
on Jasmine later, okay?

170
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,000
Excuse me.

171
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,167
I just wanted to run away.

172
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,733
Even if it was only for a little
while.

173
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:37,600
From the house,
from all the problems...

174
00:09:39,267 --> 00:09:40,933
From the pressure
you put on me, Mom.

175
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,467
What?

176
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:46,967
What are you even talking about?

177
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,800
Whenever, Mom.

178
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:54,767
Why do I have
to be perfect, Mom?

179
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:57,933
The perfect daughter?

180
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:01,767
The perfect student?

181
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:04,500
Perfect everything?

182
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,067
I can't breathe, Mom.

183
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:10,633
Hey, you!

184
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:14,100
Don't you ever talk to me
like that.

185
00:10:14,233 --> 00:10:18,033
I push you because I'm preparing
you for your future.

186
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:20,567
So your grandfather will see you

187
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:23,800
as a worthy successor
to the family business empire.

188
00:10:24,467 --> 00:10:26,167
That's what you want, Mom.

189
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:29,733
What about what I want?

190
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:34,867
Not once have you asked
about my dreams.

191
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:40,533
What I'm really happy about,

192
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:42,567
what makes me happy.

193
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,800
I'm your mother.

194
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:48,233
I know what's best for you.

195
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,333
See?

196
00:10:51,467 --> 00:10:53,600
- You never listen, Mom.
- Oh.

197
00:10:54,133 --> 00:10:56,667
You don't care about me and Dad.

198
00:10:57,767 --> 00:10:59,533
You only care about yourself.

199
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:02,367
You only think about
what you want.

200
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,200
- You disrespectful kid!
- Thea, stop!

201
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,267
Don't hurt the child.

202
00:11:25,233 --> 00:11:26,833
Why are you butting in?

203
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,700
Ashley's just your niece, right?

204
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:36,933
I know it's none of my business.

205
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,533
But don't hurt the kid.

206
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,567
She's been through enough
tonight.

207
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,167
We're not done here.

208
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:55,667
We're still going to talk.

209
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:01,967
Thea?

210
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,967
What's going on here?

211
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:11,233
I'm disciplining your daughter.

212
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:13,433
But looks like she found herself
an ally.

213
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,633
You talk to that girl.

214
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,733
Because I swear, I'm this close
to losing my patience with her.

215
00:12:21,367 --> 00:12:24,733
Come on, sweetheart.

216
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,900
Let's go home so you can rest.

217
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:33,600
Daddy...

218
00:12:35,267 --> 00:12:39,467
can I go home
with Uncle for now?

219
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,433
Are you sure?

220
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:49,733
Huh?

221
00:12:50,433 --> 00:12:53,267
You don't want to ride home with
me and your mom instead?

222
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,000
Oh, please, Edward.

223
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,233
Just let that rebellious kid go.

224
00:12:57,767 --> 00:13:01,500
She clearly wants to squeeze
herself into the family

225
00:13:01,633 --> 00:13:03,500
that blamed her
for the accident.

226
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:08,033
She'll come crawling back to us
anyway once she realizes

227
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:10,467
that family doesn't
actually want her.

228
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,767
It's okay, bro.

229
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,033
I'll take care of Ashley.

230
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,867
I won't let anything happen
to your daughter.

231
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:36,067
Just call me if there's any
problem, okay?

232
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:14,033
Go ahead, drink that.

233
00:14:15,433 --> 00:14:17,400
It'll help you calm down.

234
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:20,567
Go ahead.

235
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:35,467
Thank you, Uncle Paolo.

236
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,900
It's been a long night.

237
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:44,867
But the important thing is
you're safe.

238
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,633
I'm sorry about
what happened earlier.

239
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:57,667
I didn't mean for things to get
so messy.

240
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,667
Because of me, you all ended up
fighting.

241
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:07,233
Mom.

242
00:15:08,433 --> 00:15:09,867
Are you mad?

243
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:15,367
Honey, I'm not mad.

244
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,967
I'm just really worried about
you.

245
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:22,400
I'm really sorry, Mom.

246
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:26,233
I wish I could take back
what Ashley and I did.

247
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:30,733
Don't dwell on it anymore.

248
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:36,367
What matters is that you and
Jasmine learned your lesson.

249
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:41,033
So next time, don't do that
again, okay?

250
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:43,233
Yes.

251
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:44,800
Thank you, Uncle.

252
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:52,767
At least you
and Dad worry about me.

253
00:15:54,867 --> 00:16:00,100
Mom always meets me...

254
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:03,033
with anger and blame right away.

255
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:08,000
Even if I say something,
it's automatically wrong.

256
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:15,167
Even just breathing feels like
I'm doing something wrong.

257
00:16:16,367 --> 00:16:19,900
I'm sorry, too, sweetheart, for
how I talked to you earlier.

258
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:25,267
I got mad because I was so
scared.

259
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,367
I was terrified.

260
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:30,500
I don't want anything bad to
happen to you.

261
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:32,633
I don't want anything bad to
happen to you.

262
00:16:32,767 --> 00:16:34,400
I couldn't handle that.

263
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:36,967
I wouldn't be able to handle
losing you, Jas.

264
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,433
You know what, Ash?

265
00:16:46,267 --> 00:16:51,833
Sometimes, when parents
are scared or worried...

266
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:55,867
we end up saying things that
hurt.

267
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:58,700
But I'm sure...

268
00:17:00,167 --> 00:17:02,767
once Thea has cooled down...

269
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:06,600
she'll find a way
to understand you.

270
00:17:07,867 --> 00:17:09,067
Yes, Uncle.

271
00:17:09,767 --> 00:17:10,933
I know, Mom.

272
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,933
That's why I shouldn't have done
it.

273
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,733
I shouldn't have sneaked out.

274
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:20,267
I should've told you.

275
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:23,600
I didn't mean to make you worry.

276
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:28,333
I didn't mean to put myself...

277
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,433
or Ashley in danger.

278
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:35,867
Jas, can we not talk about
Ashley right now?

279
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:38,700
What matters
is that you're safe.

280
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:40,833
That's what matters to me.

281
00:17:42,367 --> 00:17:44,300
Thank you, Uncle Paolo.

282
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:50,300
I'm really glad
we had this talk.

283
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,567
It really made me feel better.

284
00:17:58,867 --> 00:18:00,267
I promise, Mom.

285
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:02,533
This won't happen again.

286
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:05,200
I'll talk to you next time.

287
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:07,733
I'll try harder.

288
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:10,267
Sorry.

289
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,567
I'm really sorry.

290
00:19:17,767 --> 00:19:18,933
Jas.

291
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,033
Why did you come here?

292
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,200
Auntie Marj might look for you.

293
00:19:24,967 --> 00:19:26,567
She just left.

294
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,900
She's going to visit
Uncle Jobert.

295
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:32,867
She's been on full-on mommy
patrol with me for days.

296
00:19:33,867 --> 00:19:35,633
Good thing she finally took some
me-time again.

297
00:19:36,167 --> 00:19:38,767
So now we can have our we-time.

298
00:19:40,667 --> 00:19:45,500
I just wanted to see you,
with no one else around.

299
00:19:46,967 --> 00:19:48,767
I wanted to thank you again.

300
00:19:50,067 --> 00:19:51,133
For what?

301
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,033
For taking the blame for me.

302
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:58,167
I was the one who pushed for it
in the first place.

303
00:19:58,300 --> 00:19:59,533
I dragged you into it.

304
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:03,500
And you're the one who took
responsibility.

305
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:08,833
Because...

306
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:11,700
I can handle the anger more than
you can.

307
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:16,000
I'm used to being the one
everyone gets mad at.

308
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:19,433
But you...

309
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:21,033
when I saw you
at the hospital,

310
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:22,933
when your mom
was talking to you...

311
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,000
you looked like
you were about to break.

312
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:31,467
And it was like Auntie Marj's
whole world

313
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,133
would collapse if she found out
the truth.

314
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,800
So you thought about that more
than saving yourself?

315
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:41,367
Didn't you say it yourself?
That's what best friends do.

316
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:45,000
We have each other's backs, Jas.

317
00:20:45,933 --> 00:20:47,267
And more than a best friend,

318
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,100
you're like a sister to me.

319
00:20:49,867 --> 00:20:51,867
You and your parents are family
to me, okay?

320
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:55,267
I can't stand seeing you get
hurt.

321
00:20:57,133 --> 00:20:59,000
You're my safe space here.

322
00:21:01,133 --> 00:21:04,667
You're one of the reasons I can
still breathe in this house.

323
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:09,433
You're my safe space, too, Ash.

324
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,533
You're the only breather
I have here.

325
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:23,833
So...

326
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:24,900
let's breathe?

327
00:21:25,033 --> 00:21:26,233
Ready?

328
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,167
Ready when you are.

329
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:34,467
- One... two... three...
- One... two... three...

330
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:43,900
- We got this.
- We got this.

331
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:56,600
Oh my god, Jasmine!

332
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:58,633
Your nose is bleeding!

333
00:21:59,267 --> 00:22:00,467
- Oh my god!
- It's just a little.

334
00:22:00,967 --> 00:22:03,733
Jasmine, wipe it!
Oh my God, that's a lot!

335
00:22:05,467 --> 00:22:08,000
Jas, it's not stopping!

336
00:22:13,033 --> 00:22:14,700
Give me that.

337
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:16,500
Oh my god, Jas!

338
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:21,367
It won't stop!

339
00:22:26,533 --> 00:22:27,967
It stopped, Ash.

340
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:29,367
It's fine now.

341
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:30,633
I promise.

342
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,433
Jas, there was a lot
of blood earlier.

343
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:37,700
That was scary.

344
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:39,800
Maybe I'm just tired.

345
00:22:39,933 --> 00:22:41,533
Or because it's hot.

346
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:44,333
I've had episodes
like that before.

347
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,700
But we just got into
an accident, remember?

348
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:51,500
What if it has something to do
with that?

349
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:52,967
No.

350
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:56,733
If it were serious, it wouldn't
have stopped that quickly.

351
00:22:56,867 --> 00:22:59,033
See? It's gone now.

352
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:03,233
Jas, can we just tell
Auntie Marj?

353
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:05,733
So she can have you checked out,
I'm really worried.

354
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:08,833
Please don't.

355
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,433
She's already worried
about everything.

356
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:14,300
If she finds out about this,
too,

357
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:16,400
it'll just stress her out even
more.

358
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:18,233
- But, Jas!
- Ashley!

359
00:23:19,567 --> 00:23:21,067
I'm really fine.

360
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,300
Promise.

361
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,433
I don't want to give her one
more thing to worry about.

362
00:23:26,767 --> 00:23:30,200
Let's just keep this
in between us for now.

363
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,500
Okay?

364
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:02,667
Okay, let's begin.

365
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:07,267
It's been a week since a series
of unfortunate incidents.

366
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:11,700
Hopefully, now we can all talk
like civilized Torrecampos.

367
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:15,867
I don't want tension,
I don't want walkouts,

368
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:19,133
and I definitely don't want
drama over dinner.

369
00:24:19,267 --> 00:24:21,267
Please, let's just fix this.

370
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:26,033
I completely agree, Mom.

371
00:24:27,033 --> 00:24:29,767
As for me, I've already moved on
from what happened last week.

372
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:33,100
And I understand Marj, too.

373
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:35,133
Of course, you're a mother.

374
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:37,233
Just like me, I'd panic

375
00:24:37,367 --> 00:24:39,033
if something bad happened
to my child.

376
00:24:43,033 --> 00:24:47,033
But I hope the blame doesn't
always fall on my daughter.

377
00:24:49,833 --> 00:24:53,400
She didn't mean to put herself
and Jasmine in harm's way.

378
00:24:54,733 --> 00:24:56,700
She just wanted to help Jasmine.

379
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:00,533
Her cousin has been really
stressed lately.

380
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:05,467
Maybe she feels suffocated by
how overprotective Marj can be.

381
00:25:06,767 --> 00:25:08,367
Well, to be fair,

382
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:10,667
Thea does have a point

383
00:25:11,433 --> 00:25:12,667
Marj loves hard.

384
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,600
And sometimes, that can come off
a little too strict.

385
00:25:15,733 --> 00:25:17,300
You know how teenagers are.

386
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:20,233
they need a little bit
of room to breathe.

387
00:25:26,267 --> 00:25:28,533
Is this supposed to be a
reconciliation dinner?

388
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:32,567
Because it feels like
I'm on trial.

389
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:33,833
Ah...

390
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:37,567
It's not like that, Marj.

391
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,867
I'm not saying it's your fault.

392
00:25:41,033 --> 00:25:42,867
I'm just concerned,

393
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,467
for the kids.

394
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:47,233
Concern doesn't come with
passive-aggressive comments.

395
00:25:48,367 --> 00:25:50,600
If we really want to move
forward,

396
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:53,733
then everyone should be
accountable.

397
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:56,767
Especially you with your
daughter.

398
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:05,733
Jas?

399
00:26:05,867 --> 00:26:07,533
Jas?

400
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:09,100
Are you okay?

401
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:10,300
Honey...

402
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:12,367
What are you feeling?

403
00:26:13,867 --> 00:26:14,967
Sweetheart?

404
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:16,767
- Mom...
- Yes?

405
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:17,933
I feel like...

406
00:26:18,067 --> 00:26:19,300
the room is spinning.

407
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,033
- Jasmine!
- Jasmine!

408
00:26:22,167 --> 00:26:23,267
Oh my god!

409
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,433
Jasmine!

410
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,667
Jasmine, honey!

411
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,033
- Jas!
- Sweetheart! Her medicine!

412
00:26:28,167 --> 00:26:29,500
Get her medicine! Oh my god...

413
00:26:29,633 --> 00:26:31,300
- Jas.
- Let's call...

414
00:26:33,833 --> 00:26:35,400
This is my fault.

415
00:26:35,533 --> 00:26:37,667
I should've watched her more
closely, love.

416
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:40,733
I should've noticed the symptoms
sooner.

417
00:26:40,867 --> 00:26:42,667
I should've had her checked
earlier.

418
00:26:42,833 --> 00:26:45,200
Maybe this could've been
prevented.

419
00:26:45,333 --> 00:26:46,733
This is my fault.

420
00:26:46,867 --> 00:26:48,867
My poor granddaughter.

421
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,033
She's still so young.

422
00:26:52,467 --> 00:26:53,500
Hello, Dad.

423
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,867
What? You're leaving?

424
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,033
Paolo, your daughter is sick.

425
00:26:58,167 --> 00:27:00,300
I'm sure they'll understand
that.

426
00:27:00,433 --> 00:27:02,133
If I don't go,

427
00:27:02,267 --> 00:27:03,533
everything will fall apart.

428
00:27:03,667 --> 00:27:05,433
And we'll lose the money for
Jasmine's treatment.

429
00:27:05,567 --> 00:27:06,533
Is that what you want?

430
00:27:06,667 --> 00:27:08,467
Focus on the company problem.

431
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:11,500
Then Jasmine will get
the best medical treatment.

432
00:27:11,633 --> 00:27:14,900
I don't know how I'm supposed
to handle all of this.
